{"text":{"description":[{"type":"text","value":"Gov. Greg Gianforte, elected in Nov. 2020, took office in early 2021 as Montana’s first Republican governor since 2005."},{"type":"text","value":"The governor appoints state agency heads and is ultimately responsible for the day-to-day management of government. The governor also prepares a budget proposal that serves as a starting point for the legislative appropriations process, where lawmakers determine how much the governor’s executive branch is allowed to spend."},{"type":"text","value":"Bills passed by the legislature are sent to the Governor, who can sign them into law, issue a veto, or let them become law without his signature. Vetos can be overridden by two-thirds majority votes in both the House and Senate."}]},"articles":[{"title":"A new day at DEQ and DNRC","date":"2021-01-08T20:03:58.000Z","link":"https://montanafreepress.org/2021/01/08/a-new-day-at-deq-and-dnrc/","tags":["2021 Legislature","Amanda Kaster","Chris Dorrington","Department of Environmental Quality","Department of Natural Resources and Conservation","DEQ","DNRC","Greg Gianforte"],"imageUrl":"https://montanafreepress.org/2020/10/13/the-statesman-and-the-mogul/cramer_governor13/","billTags":[],"lawmakerTags":[],"governorTags":["Greg Gianforte"]},{"title":"Gianforte budget calls for multiple tax reductions","date":"2021-01-08T01:38:28.000Z","link":"https://montanafreepress.org/2021/01/07/gianforte-budget-calls-for-multiple-tax-relief-measures/","tags":["2021 Legislature","Budget","Greg Gianforte","Kurt Alme"],"imageUrl":"https://montanafreepress.org/2020/12/11/rules-maneuvers-hint-at-a-potential-hardline-coup-in-the-house/montana-capitol_-adams_1200x675/","billTags":[],"lawmakerTags":[],"governorTags":["Greg Gianforte"]},{"title":"Gianforte signals support for state pay plan proposal","date":"2021-01-07T00:24:26.000Z","link":"https://montanafreepress.org/2021/01/06/gianforte-signals-support-for-state-pay-plan-proposal/","tags":["2021 Legislature",